us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame.interfaces

Interface FixedFramePose3DBasics

  • All Superinterfaces:
    us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Clearable, FramePose3DReadOnly, Pose3DBasics, Pose3DReadOnly, ReferenceFrameHolder, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Transformable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    FramePose3DBasics
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FramePose3D

    public interface FixedFramePose3DBasics
extends FramePose3DReadOnly, Pose3DBasics
    Write and read interface for a 3D pose expressed in a constant reference frame, i.e. this pose is always expressed in the same reference frame.

    In addition to representing a Pose3DBasics, a ReferenceFrame is associated to a FixedFramePose3DBasics. This allows, for instance, to enforce, at runtime, that operations on poses occur in the same coordinate system.

    Because a FixedFramePose3DBasics extends Pose3DBasics, it is compatible with methods only requiring Pose3DBasics. However, these methods do NOT assert that the operation occur in the proper coordinate system. Use this feature carefully and always prefer using methods requiring FixedFramePose3DBasics.

        Throws:

      • appendRotation

        default void appendRotation(FrameQuaternionReadOnly rotation)
        Appends the given rotation to this pose 3D.

        More precisely, the position part is unchanged while the orientation part is updated as follows:
        this.orientation = this.orientation * rotation

        Parameters:
        rotation - the rotation to append to this pose 3D. Not modified.
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if this and rotation are not expressed in the same reference frame.

      • interpolate

        default void interpolate(FramePose3DReadOnly other,
                         double alpha)
        Performs a linear interpolation from this to other given the percentage alpha.

        this.position = (1.0 - alpha) * this.position + alpha * other.position
        this.orientation = (1.0 - alpha) * this.orientation + alpha * other.orientation

        Parameters:
        other - the other pose 3D used for the interpolation. Not modified.
        alpha - the percentage used for the interpolation. A value of 0 will result in not modifying this, while a value of 1 is equivalent to setting this to other.
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if this and other are not expressed in the same reference frame.

      • interpolate

        default void interpolate(FramePose3DReadOnly pose1,
                         Pose3DReadOnly pose2,
                         double alpha)
        Performs a linear interpolation from pose1 to pose2 given the percentage alpha.

        this.position = (1.0 - alpha) * pose1.position + alpha * pose2.position
        this.orientation = (1.0 - alpha) * pose1.orientation + alpha * pose2.orientation

        Parameters:
        pose1 - the first pose 3D used in the interpolation. Not modified.
        pose2 - the second pose 3D used in the interpolation. Not modified.
        alpha - the percentage to use for the interpolation. A value of 0 will result in setting this to pose1, while a value of 1 is equivalent to setting this to pose2.
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if this and pose1 are not expressed in the same reference frame.

        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if this and pose2 are not expressed in the same reference frame.

        Performs a linear interpolation from pose1 to pose2 given the percentage alpha.
